                        Retirement Schemes (Member’s Request for Information on Scheme Assets)
                        Rules</docTitle><enactingFormula role="empoweringSection">(<ref href="/hk/cap426/s73">Cap. 426, section
                73</ref>)</enactingFormula><sourceNote>(Enacting provision omitted—<ref href="hk/2019/er6">E.R. 6 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote><commencementNote>[15 October 1993]<sourceNote><inline class="width_3"> </inline><ref href="/hk/1993/ln407">L.N. 407 of 1993</ref></sourceNote></commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="hk/2019/er6">E.R. 6 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438403188622_001" name="s1" reason="omittedAsSpent" startPeriod="2019-12-12" status="omitted" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><sourceNote>(Omitted as spent—<ref href="hk/2019/er6">E.R. 6 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438403188622_003" name="s2" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-12-12" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Signed notice regarded as resolution</heading><content>For the purposes of <ref>section 35(3)(b)</ref> of the Ordinance, a notice in the form specified in the <ref>Schedule</ref> signed by more than 50% of the members of a registered scheme shall be regarded as a resolution passed by such members.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403188637_002" name="s3" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-12-12" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Requesting member to be identified</heading><content>The member of a registered scheme who makes a request under <ref>section 35(3)(b)</ref> of the Ordinance shall be identified in a notice under <ref>section 2</ref>.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403188637_004" name="s4" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-12-12" status="operational" temporalId="s4"><num value="4">4.</num><heading>Names and identity card numbers to be written</heading><leadIn>A person’s signature, other than the signature of the member making the request under <ref>section 35(3)(b)</ref> of the Ordinance, on a notice referred to in <ref>section 2</ref> shall not be effective for the purpose of that section unless—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438412493988_012" name="a" temporalId="s4_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>the full name of the person; and</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438412493988_020" name="b" temporalId="s4_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>the number of the identity card (if any) issued to that person under the Registration of Persons Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap177">Cap. 177</ref>),</content></paragraph><continued>are written legibly against the signature.</continued></section><section id="ID_1438403188653_002" name="s5" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-12-12" status="operational" temporalId="s5"><num value="5">5.</num><heading>More than 1 notice</heading><content>A resolution referred to in <ref>section 2</ref> may be constituted by more than 1 notice provided each such notice is in the form specified in the <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403188653_004" name="s6" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-12-12" status="operational" temporalId="s6"><num value="6">6.</num><heading>Determination of majority</heading><subsection id="ID_1438412494019_004" name="1" temporalId="s6_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content>Where on the day on which a notice referred to in <ref>section 2</ref> is given to the designated person of a registered scheme, the number of persons who have signed the notice and who are members of the scheme exceeds 50% of the number of the members of that scheme as on that day, the resolution constituted by such notice shall be regarded as being passed on that day.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438412494019_012" name="2" temporalId="s6_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>In calculating the number of persons who have signed a notice referred to in <ref>section 2</ref> the member making the request for information by the notice shall be included.</content></subsection></section><schedule id="ID_1438403188669_002" name="sch0" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-12-12" status="operational" temporalId="sch0"><num value="0">Schedule</num><note class="align_right" role="crossReferences" type="inline">[<ref href="/hk/cap426F/s2">ss.
                2</ref> &amp; <ref href="/hk/cap426F/s5">5</ref>]</note><crossHeading><inline class="not_bold">Notice</inline></crossHeading><text>
            
